babyDuckling.name: Baby Duckling
babyDuckling.description: A tiny, adorable source of passive quacks. Peep!

breadScavenger.name: Bread Scavenger
breadScavenger.description: This duck knows where all the discarded bread is.

keyboardWarrior.name: Quack-Powered Keyboard Warrior
keyboardWarrior.description: Aggressively quacks online, somehow generating QP.

duckArmyRecruit.name: Duck Army Recruit
duckArmyRecruit.description: One of many. They march for QP.

memeAiDuck.name: Meme-Generating AI Duck
memeAiDuck.description: This advanced AI churns out viral duck memes, and QP.

ducktopiaPortal.name: Ducktopia Portal
ducktopiaPortal.description: Opens a rift to a dimension of pure quack energy.

gigachadDuck.name: Gigachad Duck
gigachadDuck.description: This duck didn't skip beak day. Flexes for massive QP.

philosoRaptorDuck.name: Philoso-Raptor Duck
philosoRaptorDuck.description: Ponders the meaning of quack, accidentally discovers QP sources.

ducktrixCodeStream.name: Ducktrix Code Stream
ducktrixCodeStream.description: It's all just falling green ducks... and QP.

cosmicDuckEgg.name: Cosmic Duck Egg
cosmicDuckEgg.description: An egg laid by a celestial duck. Radiates immense QP. Requires Level 8.

voidQuacker.name: Void Quacker
voidQuacker.description: Quacks from the void itself. Unsettling. Requires Level 15.

neuralNetDuck.name: Neural Net Duck Assimilator
neuralNetDuck.description: A self-aware AI duck network that has begun to understand the underlying quack-fabric of reality. Requires Level 22.

duckemon_013.name: Wheeduck
duckemon_013.description: A fuzzy little worm-duck. Mostly harmless, but watch out for its tiny bill-sting!

duckemon_014.name: Duckoon
duckemon_014.description: Hardening its shell, this duck awaits its glorious transformation. Doesn't move much.

duckemon_015.name: Beedrilluck
duckemon_015.description: A fearsome hornet-duck with three poisonous drill-beaks. Approach with extreme caution!

duckemon_016.name: Pidgefluff
duckemon_016.description: A common bird-duck, known for its gentle cooing and sudden gusts of wind.

duckemon_017.name: Pidgeottoot
duckemon_017.description: This duck claims a large territory and defends it fiercely with sharp squawks.

duckemon_018.name: Pidgeoquack
duckemon_018.description: Flies at Mach 2 speed, searching for prey with its keen eyesight. A majestic sky-duck.

duckemon_019.name: Ratattail
duckemon_019.description: Small and quick, this duck's sharp fangs can gnaw through almost anything. Often found near bins.

duckemon_020.name: Ratiquack
duckemon_020.description: Its sturdy fangs can topple concrete buildings. If you see one, your cheese is not safe.

duckemon_021.name: Spearowbill
duckemon_021.description: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.

duckemon_022.name: Fearowflight
duckemon_022.description: With its magnificent and TOP wings, it can keep aloft without ever having to land for rest.

duckemon_023.name: Snekduck
duckemon_023.description: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of Pidgefluffs and Spearowbills.

duckemon_024.name: Kobraduck
duckemon_024.description: The pattern on its belly is for intimidation. It constricts foes while injecting venom.

duckemon_025.name: Pikachirp
duckemon_025.description: It stores electricity in its cheek pouches. When it's angry, it unleashes stored lightning.

duckemon_026.name: Raichirp
duckemon_026.description: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.

duckemon_027.name: Sandshrewd
duckemon_027.description: It burrows and lives underground. If threatened, it curls itself up into a protective ball.

duckemon_028.name: Sandslashbill
duckemon_028.description: Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.

duckemon_029.name: Nidoqueenling
duckemon_029.description: Small and timid, its horn is not yet fully developed. The barb secretes a potent poison.

duckemon_030.name: Nidorhina
duckemon_030.description: The female's horn develops slowly. Prefers physical attacks such as clawing and biting.

duckemon_031.name: Nidoqueenbill
duckemon_031.description: Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.

duckemon_032.name: Nidokingling
duckemon_032.description: It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.

duckemon_033.name: Nidorayno
duckemon_033.description: An aggressive Duckemon that jabs with its poisonous horn. Quick to anger.

duckemon_034.name: Nidoemperor
duckemon_034.description: Its thick hide protects it from attacks. It is adept at sending foes flying with harsh tackles.

duckemon_035.name: Clefairywisp
duckemon_035.description: Its adorable behavior and cry make it highly popular. Said to be found where moonlight gathers.

duckemon_036.name: Clefablewisp
duckemon_036.description: A timid fairy Duckemon that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.

duckemon_037.name: Vulpquack
duckemon_037.description: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.

duckemon_038.name: Ninetailflame
duckemon_038.description: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1000-year curse.

duckemon_039.name: Jigglyplume
duckemon_039.description: When its huge eyes waver, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

duckemon_040.name: Wigglyplume
duckemon_040.description: Its body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.

duckemon_041.name: Zoobat
duckemon_041.description: Forms colonies in perpetually dark places. Uses ultrasonic waves to identify and approach targets.

duckemon_042.name: Golbatwing
duckemon_042.description: Once it strikes, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.

duckemon_043.name: Oddprout
duckemon_043.description: During the day, it keeps its face buried in the ground. At night, it wanders around sowing its seeds.

duckemon_044.name: Gloomspore
duckemon_044.description: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn't drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.

duckemon_045.name: Vileplumecloud
duckemon_045.description: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.

duckemon_046.name: Parashroom
duckemon_046.description: Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by drawing nutrients from the host.

duckemon_047.name: Parasectoid
duckemon_047.description: A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.

duckemon_048.name: Venonatfly
duckemon_048.description: Its large eyes act as radar. In a dark place, a Venonatfly uses its eyes to find its way.

duckemon_049.name: Venomothdust
duckemon_049.description: The dust-like scales covering its wings are color-coded to indicate the kinds of poison it has.

duckemon_050.name: Digduglett
duckemon_050.description: Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears aboveground.

duckemon_051.name: Dugtrioquack
duckemon_051.description: A team of Digduglett triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.

duckemon_052.name: Meowthpurr
duckemon_052.description: Adores circular objects. Wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.

duckemon_053.name: Persimew II
duckemon_053.description: Its lithe muscles allow it to walk without making a sound. It attacks stealthily.

duckemon_054.name: Psyquack
duckemon_054.description: It has mystical powers but doesn't recall that it has used them. That is why it always looks puzzled.

duckemon_055.name: Golduckbill
duckemon_055.description: Often seen swimming elegantly by lakes. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster Kappa.

duckemon_056.name: Mankeydoodle
duckemon_056.description: Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment then thrashing away the next instant.

duckemon_057.name: Primeapexr
duckemon_057.description: Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it is caught.

duckemon_058.name: Growlhowl
duckemon_058.description: Very friendly and faithful to people. It will try to repel enemies by barking and biting.

duckemon_059.name: Arcaninebark
duckemon_059.description: A Duckemon that has been admired since the past for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.

duckemon_060.name: Poliwaddle
duckemon_060.description: Its newly grown legs prevent it from walking well. It appears to prefer swimming over walking.

duckemon_061.name: Poliwhirlpool
duckemon_061.description: Capable of living in or out of water. When out of water, it sweats to keep its body slimy.

duckemon_062.name: Poliwrathwave
duckemon_062.description: An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breaststroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.

duckemon_063.name: Abraquack
duckemon_063.description: Sleeps 18 hours a day. If it senses danger, it will teleport itself to safety even as it sleeps.

duckemon_064.name: Kadabracadabra
duckemon_064.description: It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being nearby.

duckemon_065.name: Alakazamp
duckemon_065.description: Its brain can outperform a super-computer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5,000.

duckemon_066.name: Machopchop
duckemon_066.description: Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.

duckemon_067.name: Machokeduck
duckemon_067.description: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

duckemon_068.name: Machampflex
duckemon_068.description: Using its four ruggedly developed arms, it launches furious blows that can demolish mountains.

duckemon_069.name: Bellbloom
duckemon_069.description: A carnivorous Duckemon that traps and eats bugs. It appears to use its root feet to replenish moisture.

duckemon_070.name: Weepinbelljar
duckemon_070.description: It spits out PoisonPowder to immobilize the target and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.

duckemon_071.name: Victreebelltrap
duckemon_071.description: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.

duckemon_072.name: Tentacoolio
duckemon_072.description: Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by its stinging acid.

duckemon_073.name: Quacktonium Core
duckemon_073.description: A pulsating core of unstable quack energy. Handle with care, or don't.

duckemon_074.name: CryoDuck Cryolophosaurus
duckemon_074.description: An ancient duck frozen in time, now thawed and quacking with icy breath.

duckemon_075.name: RoboDuck Warden
duckemon_075.description: A cybernetic guardian duck, programmed to protect the timeline from rogue QP anomalies.

duckemon_076.name: Duckemon #76
duckemon_076.description: An undiscovered species of Duckemon. Its powers are unknown.
